Financially, the shortage of jobs resulting from the global market’s effect on global economy is a drag on developing a medium and high tech industry or balanced economy in Hungary. Agriculture and farming, as in the US, subsidies are supported by the government to keep rural areas viable. An important factor to the future of Hungary is the condition of its transportation infrastructure. The vast network of tunnels and caverns north to northwest is vital in enlarging trade in the nation’s heartland.

Jobless for college graduates is a classic middle class harbinger of doom or famine will strike sooner than later. Same in the US. The jobless with such companies as General Electric’s CEO that wants people to die to save money, up-skilling workers for original and flexibility boiling their bodies when asked, or a tax code that allows wealthy company owners to injest billions and shift them to tax shelters is hardly acceptable and the CEO strolls clean.

The frailties of living as a nation are best kept out of the market-making choices of the markets.
